        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Royal Gardens Kew</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Aug 5 /69.</date>
                    <salute>Dear Darwin</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I thought you would be interested to know that Dr Cunningham has brought the upper &amp; lower jaws of an Anoplotherium from the Gallegas river— Huxley shewed me them today.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>I went to Brighton yesterday &amp; saw Hallett’s wheat crops.— his results by Selection are very striking—<ref target="#foot.f2"/> He finds by experiment that having advanced to a certain point in improving the quality in a desired direction he can get no further, &amp; that then the power of varying in other directions is much reduced— thus, the Le Couteur wheat which,—itself a very highly improved strain, he has tried in vain to break— he can however from common wheats raise a strain far superior to LeCouteurs,—<ref target="#foot.f3"/> I was much pleased with the man &amp; his methods;—though not altogether a Scientific observer &amp; experimenter,—I think he is a sound &amp; good one in many respects.— He is drawing up a paper for the British Association.<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p>
<p>Has this been proved <hi rend="underline">on wheats</hi> before?</p>
<p>Huxley is arranging all his Darwinian papers for republication—<ref target="#foot.f5"/> he is a <hi rend="underline">most</hi> wonderful man—&amp; I am beginning to feel quite infantine beside him!— I have read his answer to Congreve,—it is crushing, but too discursive as it struck me—<ref target="#foot.f6"/></p>
<p>I have not seen the N. B. which has a “fling at me” as you call it—<ref target="#foot.f7"/> tell me “on your soul” should I see it?— I have not the smallest curiosity to do so except you think it merits it in any way, great or small. I have no time for mere literature &amp; no mood for worry: &amp; I still dream at times that I have the address to deliver!.<ref target="#foot.f8"/></p>
<p>What did you think of Govt. offering, &amp; Sabine’s accepting, K.C.B.—<ref target="#foot.f9"/> I do think that the chucking the bauble into the poor man’s Coffin—so to speak—is in the most atrocious bad taste—&amp; worse than that is the exhibition of eternal childhood in the aged philosopher’s clutching at it— I should have refused it &amp; written to the Times! I am sure, if he deserved it at all, he did so 20 years ago, when it would have been a gracious acknowledgment of public services.</p>
<p>I am anxious to hear how you are now that you are at home? &amp; Mrs Darwin &amp; George.<ref target="#foot.f10"/></p>
<p>Ever yrs affec | J D Hooker</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
